// AGENDA
Introduction to open source concurrency framework Disruptor.Net and how to use it for high performance concurrent programming. I will try to explain some common bottlenecks in concurrent applications and how Disruptor overcomes these and thereby a gentle introduction to lockless concurrent programming. Will also give examples of how I have used Disruptor.Net and samples of applications and architectures it can be used with. Even though you are not planning on using Disruptor this could give you insights into some issues in the world of concurrent programming you might not be aware of.

// BIO
Rasmus Nygaard Andersen is a software architect and consultant at Comiit. He specializes in high performance systems, big-data and cloud solutions on the .Net and Java platform. He has experience with developing software within a wide range of domains like finance, windmills, farming, energy, education etc. He loves elegant code and creating software that does not suck.
